title: Policy6005(s4)
type: text/vnd.tiddlywiki

Enrolling in Region 8 Public Schools: The school principal, in consultation with the members of the school's instructional team, will make the decision about the students' grade and/or course level placement based on the student's performance on district assessments and/or universal screening tools. The principal will also review and consider any current standardized student assessment results provided by the parent/guardian. The final decision for grade and/or course level placement will be made by the school principal.
